tariff simulator:
----------------

Reads input file with call minutes and a tariff and returns the total cost of the bill.
Also supports finding the best tariff for a single o various monthly bills.

Assumptions:
-----------
bills/ should have the monthly bills, each bill having the minutes for each call.
tariffs.py has the tariffs you want to test.
All tariffs have the same cost for ANY operator.
SMS are out.

sample usage:
./tariff.py data tariff : calculates the bill for month 'bills/data' with tariff 'tariff'
./tariff.py data best : calculates the best tariff for month 'bills/data'
./tariff.py all best : calculates the best tariff for all monthly bills in bills/
./tariff.py all tariff : calculates the total bill for tariff 'tariff' with all monthly bills in bills/
